HEADWORD: Pomaceous
<hw>Po*ma"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>ponum</ets> an apple.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Like an apple or pear; producing pomes.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to a suborder
(<subord>Pome⟦ae⟧</subord>) of rosaceous plants, which includes the true
thorn trees, the quinces, service berries, medlars, and loquats, as well
as the apples, pears, crabs, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Like pomace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pomade</ent>⟦br⟧
